      {
         "id": "SECTION_prerequisites",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><span id=\"htZoomImageMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htChartMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htAmericaAbyaYalaMsg\"></span> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('160fb48c-1711-491e-a1aa-e1257e7889af'); return false;\">Porto-Gonçalves, Carlos Walter, <htdate0>, pp. 39-43</a>).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2011",
                     "month": "",
                     "day": ""
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nThis text continues the teachings of the previous chapter (<htcite0>). Therefore, we suggest you study it before proceeding.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "f1e985f6-ee34-407a-9b47-7ac1a3c8bc48",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "First Steps – Volume II",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nLet's begin this text with a practice exercise.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_lab_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_lab question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-microscope\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_lab\"><b>Practice 1: Mirroring</b><br /><br />Take a flat mirror and look into it.</div></div></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "After looking at yourself in it, reflect:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: My distance is...</b><br /><br />What is the distance of your image in the mirror?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_Other_Side",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### On the other side\n\nA glass mirror is not the only way we have of reflecting our images. Another place where we can observe reflections is a water reservoir (**Figure 1**), like the one that has existed in Tikal, Guatemala (*Abya Yala*) for centuries (<htcite0>):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "7ee4e8f6-3f68-4dbc-ad17-3b39f9964ef2",
                     "text": "Parque Nacional Tikal",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"gc\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('gc', '0%')\" src=\"images/Tikal/TikalReservorio.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\" style=\"width:60%\"/><b>Figure 1</b>: Water reservoir in Tikal, Guatemala (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('7ee4e8f6-3f68-4dbc-ad17-3b39f9964ef2'); return false;\">Parque Nacional Tikal</a>). Photo taken on <htdate0>, during a visit to the site.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2015",
                     "month": "10",
                     "day": "22"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Notice that, in **Figure 1**, although the reservoir's sign is in the foreground, it is possible to observe, in the background of the image, the trees reflected in the water. The mirror and the water reservoir share a common characteristic regarding the images we see in them: the distance of the tree's image in the reservoir is equal to the distance from the tree to it. Similarly, the image in the mirror is at the same distance from the mirror as you are from it.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: Drawing</b><br /><br />So far, we have worked with numbers that moved in one direction. From now on, we will also begin to work with elements that move in the opposite direction.<br /><br />How would you use numbers to represent this scenario?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_mirroring",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Extending\n\n#### Let's look at an image\n\nThe distance of our image, when reflected, will be our starting point to extend the numbers we use. Let's make a graph where a mirror is in the center, an object is placed on the right, and its image is on the left:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg width=\"500\" height=\"100\"  fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"2\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"490\" y2=\"75\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <line x1=\"50\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"90\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"130\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"130\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"170\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"170\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"210\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"210\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"250\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"290\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"290\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"330\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"330\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"370\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"370\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"410\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"450\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"450\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#00FF00\"></circle> <circle cx=\"450\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#00FF00\"></circle> <line x1=\"250\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"5\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"7\" />  </svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 1</b>: Representation of a mirror in the center reflecting, on the left, an image that is on its right.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Observe **Graph 1** and do the following practice:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_lab_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_lab question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-microscope\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_lab\"><b>Practice 2: Mirroring</b><br /><br />1. Count how many marks we have from the mirror, in the center, to the green circle on the right;<br /><br />2. Now, count how many marks we have from the mirror to the green circle on the left.</div></div></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "As can be seen, because the mirror is flat, the distance is the same on the right and on the left.\n\nIn the first chapter of the *First Steps* section, we learned to count starting from zero and saw that numbers tend to infinity on the right (<htcite0>). With this teaching, we can complete one side of **Graph 1**:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b5efc8f9-c268-430f-9681-7a43848ee48e",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "First Steps",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg width=\"500\" height=\"100\"  fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"2\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"490\" y2=\"75\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <line x1=\"50\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"90\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"130\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"130\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"170\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"170\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"210\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"210\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"250\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"290\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"290\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"330\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"330\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"370\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"370\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"410\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"450\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"450\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#00FF00\"></circle> <circle cx=\"450\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#00FF00\"></circle> <line x1=\"250\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"5\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"7\" /> <text x=\"245\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">0</text> <text x=\"285\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">1</text> <text x=\"325\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">2</text> <text x=\"365\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">3</text> <text x=\"405\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">4</text> <text x=\"445\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">5</text> </svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 2</b>: Representation of a mirror in the center reflecting, on the left, an image that is on its right, with numbers measuring the distance to the right.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 3: Decreasing</b><br /><br />We know that on the left side, we have the same number of numbers as on the right side. Furthermore, we know that numbers increase from left to right.<br /><br />With this data, how would you fill in the numbers on the left?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Filling in on the left\n\n**Reflection 3** gives us the details we need to continue building **Graph 2**. So, let's see:\n- We need to place five numbers on the left side;\n- We cannot place numbers starting from zero further to the left, as we already have zero in the center;\n- We know that numbers increase as we move to the right.\n\nPutting all this together, we can update **Graph 2** as follows:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg width=\"500\" height=\"100\"  fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"8\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"490\" y2=\"75\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" marker-start=\"url(#arrow)\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <line x1=\"50\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"90\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"90\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"130\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"130\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"170\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"170\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"210\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"210\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"250\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"290\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"290\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"330\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"330\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"370\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"370\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"410\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"410\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"450\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"450\" y2=\"85\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#00FF00\"></circle> <circle cx=\"450\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#00FF00\"></circle> <line x1=\"250\" y1=\"75\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"5\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"7\" /> <text x=\"45\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">5</text> <text x=\"85\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">4</text> <text x=\"125\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">3</text> <text x=\"165\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">2</text> <text x=\"205\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">1</text> <text x=\"245\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">0</text> <text x=\"285\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">1</text> <text x=\"325\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">2</text> <text x=\"365\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">3</text> <text x=\"405\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">4</text> <text x=\"445\" y=\"99\" font-size=\"1.5em\">5</text> </svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 3</b>: Representation of a mirror in the center reflecting, on the left, an image that is on its right, with numbers measuring the distance.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 4: Turn the...</b><br /><br />Suppose I have not informed you where the original object and the image are in <b>Graph 3</b>. Now, reflect:<br /><br />If I say that the object was placed at distance 5, would that be enough to know that the object is on the right?<br /><br />Would it be necessary to provide more information, in addition to the distance, for you to know where it is?<br /><br />Does the fact that the numbers are written in reverse order help you identify anything?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      }
   ],
   "exercise_v2": [
      {
         "question": "A distância de nossa imagem em um espelho ou um reservatório de água é igual a distância que estamos deles?",
         "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
         "additionalInfo": "Um espelho plano ou um reservatório de água sempre reproduzem nossa imagem a mesma distância que estamos deles, isto quer dizer, que se estivermos a 30 centímetros de um deles, nossa imagem estará a 60 centímetros de nós (30 centímetros até o espelho, e 30 centímetros do espelho até a imagen."
      }
   ],
   "game_v2": null,
   "date_time": null
}
